    thinking: "**Defining the STT Web Service**\n\nI\'m currently focused on crafting a comprehensive PRD for the IT service. My goal is to use Web Speech API to build an internal web service that transcribes and saves meeting audio in real-time. I\'m prioritizing thoroughness in defining the product requirements.\n\n\n**Refining the PRD Structure**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the PRD\'s structure, aiming for AI Studio compatibility using \'Vibe Coding\'. I need to ensure the document is readily copied and used as markdown code blocks. The \"Calibration\" section emphasizes the need for clarifying questions before drafting the PRD; I need to determine the user\'s current status and tailor my approach accordingly: are they ready for the meeting, receiving the PRD, or answering questions? My current goal is now in question.\n\n\n**Formulating Essential Questions**\n\nI\'ve got a draft PRD in place, but I\'m unsure whether to refine it immediately or to take this turn for questions. Given the user\'s intent to build this as an AI Studio \'Vibe Coding\' service, and their request for a Markdown-formatted PRD ready for direct pasting, I need to extract crucial details. I\'m focused on formulating a series of 3-4 progressive questions to obtain the essential information needed to make the PRD perfect.\n\n\n**Crafting Welcoming Questions**\n\nI\'m now shifting to a more welcoming and professional tone, as befitting an E-Land Hotel PM. I will refine the approach into a sequence of questions, starting with a polite and detailed introduction. I plan to incorporate a brief, insightful feedback on the given plan. Then, I will move to ask three or more progressive questions to formulate a truly custom PRD.\n\n\n\n**Probing Technical Nuances**\n\nI\'m now delving into the technical aspects. Specifically, I need to know if speaker diarization or indication is necessary, given Web Speech API\'s limitations, and if we should offer manual speaker distinction. Also, I must determine if timestamping of long sentences is required. Finally, I\'m examining UX considerations, probing about data compression, external integrations, and the future integration of features like meeting summarization with Gemini API.\n\n\n**Defining Project Metadata**\n\nI\'m considering whether I should update metadata.json now, even though I\'m still in the PRD planning and calibration phase, pre-development. I think it\'s wise to define the app name and description proactively. I\'ve decided this project will be named \"E-Land Hotel Meeting Recorder,\" with the description: \"Real-time meeting audio recording and management service (using Chrome\'s Web Speech API).\" I\'ll proceed with these details.\n\n\n"
