    thinking: "**Defining Core Logic**\n\nI\'m now focusing on defining the `/src/components/Recorder.tsx` file. My goal is to determine the core logic for the Chrome Web Speech API within a React context. I need to understand how standard Speech Recognition is instantiated, starting with the `window.SpeechRecognition` object.\n\n\n**Declaring Interface and Keep-Alive**\n\nI\'ve declared a TypeScript interface for `SpeechRecognition` to ensure type safety. Now, I\'m designing the \"Keep-Alive\" logic to prevent automatic termination during periods of silence. I instantiated `webkitSpeechRecognition` or `SpeechRecognition` inside a ref, preserving it across renders. Also, I\'ve enabled continuous listening with `recognition.continuous = true;`, interim results with `recognition.interimResults = true;`, and set the language to Korean with `recognition.lang = \'ko-KR\';`.\n\n\n**Tracing Transcript Reception**\n\nI\'m now tracing the transcript reception logic and how to handle it when `recognition.continuous = true`. The `onresult` event handler reveals that `isFinal` indicates the accumulation of final text. I want to append final transcripts to state to avoid resetting the text area. The results array grows, and joining `isFinal` results gives the entire transcript for a session. However, session restarts reset the array, so now I need to figure out how to handle that.\n\n\n**Refining Final Transcript Handling**\n\nI\'m now refining the logic for handling final transcripts and avoiding duplication. I will maintain a state or ref called `accumulatedTranscript`, appending finalized text when the recognition starts or restarts. I\'m examining the `onresult` event, specifically `event.resultIndex`. I\'ve realized that iterating from this index onward lets me correctly identify and append any new finalized segment. I am confident that the `event.resultIndex` is the first index in the results list that has changed, so any `isFinal` at or after `event.resultIndex` is a new finalized segment!\n\n\n**Revising Transcript Accumulation**\n\nI\'m revisiting the transcript accumulation logic because the existing approach might duplicate or miss segments. I\'m focusing on ensuring accuracy with `event.resultIndex` and the results array length. I\'m considering accumulating session transcripts in `onresult` to capture and preserve all segments, both final and interim. I\'m now testing the revised loop, which includes every index to ensure robust transcript handling, addressing potential browser-specific variations.\n\n\n**Finalizing Session Handling**\n\nI\'m now solidifying the session handling. The key is in accurately tracking all finalized text. I\'ve realized that `historyOfPreviousSessionsText + currentSessionFinal` provides the complete transcript. When the session ends, I commit `currentSessionFinal` to `historyOfPreviousSessionsText` before restarting. I\'m storing finalized text from previous sessions in `accruedTextRef.current`. I\'m using `accruedTextRef.current + sessionFinal` for the live finalized text. When `onend` triggers during a recording, I save the session\'s final text.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the Speech Recognition & Recording controller (`/src/components/Recorder.tsx`). It leverages Chrome\'s `window.webkitSpeechRecognition` with the keep-alive (auto-restart) system to bypass silent pauses, supports multilanguage recording (Korean/English/Japanese), features a duration counter, showcases a glowing audio wave animation, and handles permission rejections/safeguards gracefully."
