  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing the New Component**\n\nI\'m thinking about the new component, `/src/components/AISummaryPanel.tsx`. It needs to display an AI summary and action items, specifically requested by the user during calibration. This component is key for this design stage, acting as an AI core summary panel. I\'m focusing on its responsibilities and presentation.\n\n\n**Analyzing Markdown Rendering**\n\nI\'m now focused on rendering Markdown elegantly in the new component. I\'m considering several approaches: direct rendering helpers, leveraging `react-markdown` (checking its presence in `package.json` first), or even crafting a light, custom Markdown parser with regex for simplicity. The prompt emphasized that it wasn\'t pre-installed, so I have to install it if I wish to use it, or write a custom hook. I think a regex-based plain text markdown formatter hook seems like a great idea.\n\n\n**Crafting the Markdown Renderer**\n\nI\'ve decided on a custom, lightweight Markdown renderer directly within `/src/components/AISummaryPanel.tsx`. The goal is a fast, dependency-free solution that offers full control over Tailwind styling. I\'m focusing on parsing common markdown elements like headers (`###`, `##`, etc.) and lists, generating styled React blocks with custom accents, lists, and blockquotes. This approach ensures a bespoke visual interface without external library dependencies. I can handle tailwind easily by writing the right hooks.\n\nI am also thinking about a copying feature for the component, inspired by the request for an HTML archive template copy format. I\'m considering providing two options: \"Copy as Rich HTML\", which creates a formatted HTML document, and a plain text copy function.\n\n\n**Implementing HTML Formatting**\n\nI\'m now focusing on a new \"Copy as Rich HTML\" feature for the AI summary panel. My plan is to convert the Markdown content into styled HTML, suitable for direct pasting into email clients and word processors. The goal is a premium, polished look using a color palette of Navy, Gold, and Charcoal, which could be extremely valuable for internal communications. I\'m prioritizing inline styles for maximum compatibility. I\'ll translate markdown headers and bullet points into styled HTML elements.\n\n\n**Refining HTML Style Output**\n\nI\'m now refining the HTML output. I\'ve integrated styling directly into the HTML elements. I\'m using inline styles that align with the color palette: Navy, Gold, and Charcoal. I\'m focusing on markdown elements to ensure a premium look. Headers are now styled correctly. Bullet points and paragraphs are handled. I\'m using a responsive font and spacing.\n\n\n**Formatting the HTML Output**\n\nI\'m now integrating the provided HTML structure, tailoring it for the \"Copy as Rich HTML\" feature. I\'m focusing on directly injecting the summary content within this template, ensuring a polished, professional look. My goal is for this output to be readily usable and visually appealing for various applications.\n\n\n**Integrating HTML Tables**\n\nI\'m now integrating HTML tables into the HTML output for the \"Copy as Rich HTML\" feature. I\'m focusing on incorporating a styled table structure for meeting details. I am also working on parsing the Markdown to render the HTML. I\'ll translate markdown into the HTML to show the tables and information.\n\nI\'m working to integrate a styled table structure for meeting details into the HTML output, for a polished appearance. The goal is to format meeting details, summaries, and action items in a readable format.\n\n\n**Implementing Clipboard Rich Text**\n\nI\'m now implementing the rich text copy-to-clipboard functionality. My focus is ensuring formatted HTML is correctly copied, complete with styles. I\'m leveraging the clipboard API to handle `text/html` and `text/plain` formats, allowing seamless pasting into email clients. I\'m crafting a dedicated function, `copyRichHtmlToClipboard`, to manage this complex process.\n\n\n**Refining Clipboard Functionality**\n\nI\'m now refining the clipboard functionality to handle rich text and plain text more robustly. I\'m focusing on ensuring graceful fallbacks when the ClipboardItem API fails, defaulting to plain text copying. I\'m implementing error handling within `copyRichHtmlToClipboard` to catch and manage any issues with clipboard access, improving overall usability. I\'m also ensuring the code can catch various problems.\n\n\n**Parsing Markdown Headings**\n\nI\'m now focusing on parsing and rendering markdown headings of varying levels within the component. I\'m focusing on parsing bold text too. I\'m integrating logic to accurately identify and style `#`, `##`, and `###` headings with appropriate semantic HTML tags and visual styling, including font size and color. I\'m also ensuring a robust parsing to gracefully handle these elements.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the AI Summary Panel component (`/src/components/AISummaryPanel.tsx`). It features a structural holder for AI summarized data, renders markdown paragraphs into nice Tailwind elements with high-contrast text, provides interactive checkable To-Do list items, and offers copy options (such as direct Markdown copy, or rich inline-styled HTML copy for E-Land Hotel newsletter memos)."
