  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing Calendar View**\n\nI\'m currently focused on designing a \"View as Calendar\" toggle for the left sidebar. My goal is to allow users to filter meetings by date within the Month/Week view. I\'m exploring different layouts for the calendar widget, possibly integrating it at the bottom of the sidebar or as a toggle mode. I want to create something elegant and user-friendly.\n\n\n**Refining Calendar Integration**\n\nI\'m now leaning towards a toggle that switches the entire sidebar view between a list and an interactive calendar. This would provide a more dedicated calendar experience. The idea is to have a polished and responsive calendar UI directly within the sidebar, offering intuitive date selection and filtering. The sidebar UI will switch between the two views when the toggle is activated.\n\n\n**Implementing Dual-Mode Sidebar**\n\nI\'ve decided on a dual-mode sidebar approach: \"List View\" and \"Calendar View\" toggled at the bottom. The \"\354\272\230\353\246\260\353\215\224 \353\263\264\352\270\260\" will replace the meeting list with a fully interactive monthly/weekly calendar featuring date indicators. I will give users options to switch between Month/Week. I\'m focusing on ensuring it\'s both space-efficient and exceptionally usable within the sidebar.\n\n\n**Constructing Calendar Logic**\n\nI\'m now fully immersed in building the core logic for the month/week calendar. I\'m focusing on a dependency-free TypeScript/React implementation to keep it robust. I\'m focusing on implementing the monthly and weekly grid generation, with navigation to the previous/next periods. Date parsing and matching of meeting dates, in `YYYY-MM-DD` format, are the current focus to enable filtering based on the selected date. I\'m aiming for a magnificent, beautiful, and feature-rich calendar component.\n\n\n**Integrating Calendar Features**\n\nI\'m now integrating the calendar feature into the sidebar, focusing on an elegant design to avoid clutter. I\'ve decided to enable meeting filtering. Selecting a date in the calendar will filter the meeting list to that date, with a \"Show All\" option to clear filters. I\'m carefully defining the state for this calendar view in `Sidebar.tsx`, including `viewMode`, `calendarViewType`, `currentDate`, and `selectedDateStr` for filtering. I am writing a helper to format dates to `YYYY-MM-DD`.\n\n\n**Visualizing Calendar Display**\n\nI\'ve just focused on the ideal width, finding that 320px sidebar allows for a compact calendar. I\'ve been designing month/week view grids: the navigation header should have `[ < ] 2026\353\205\204 5\354\233\224 [ > ]` with toggle buttons for `[ \354\233\224\352\260\204 ] [ \354\243\274\352\260\204 ]`. The weekday labels are: `\354\235\274 \354\233\224 \355\231\224 \354\210\230 \353\252\251 \352\270\210 \355\206\240`, and I\'m ready to calculate the grid layout.\n\n\n**Generating Week Views**\n\nI\'m now implementing the week view cells, ensuring it displays the 7 days containing the current date, from Sunday to Saturday. I\'m focusing on calculating the Sunday of the week to correctly generate the week\'s dates.\nI am focused on the logic for the Week View, and it\'s looking extremely polished! I am also working on creating a helper to generate the month\'s days.\n\n\n**Refining Calendar Logic**\n\nI\'ve just implemented helper functions for generating month and week views. The month view logic ensures a consistent 42-cell grid. The week view function accurately generates the seven days of the week, starting from Sunday. I\'m now focusing on user interactions: filtering meetings by the selected date, displaying a count of meetings for the selected date, and a message with a button for new meetings if none exist.\n\n\n**Enhancing Date Selection**\n\nI\'m thrilled with the user experience \342\200\223 it\'s going to be exceptional! I\'m adding an event that triggers `onNewMeeting()` and presets the date in the new meeting form to the selected date. I\'ll need to modify the `handleNewMeeting` function in `App.tsx` to accept an optional `presetDate` string. I\'m excited about how this will streamline the new meeting process.\n\n\n**Designing Toggle Component**\n\nI\'m now focused on building the \"List View\" and \"Calendar View\" toggle. I am implementing a custom design for the control bar at the bottom of the sidebar, including smooth hovering effects. I\'m aiming for a visually appealing and intuitive toggle switch, with a focus on a clean and elegant look. The control bar will sit right above the systems environment line.\n\n\n**Visualizing Calendar Display**\n\nI\'m now determining what to show when the calendar view is active. I plan to render the calendar grid with navigation, the month/week toggle, and then the filtered meeting list for a selected date. If no date is selected, the grid alone will render. I\'ll include indicators on dates with meetings and allow direct selection for viewing and editing. I\'m focusing on ensuring it\'s space-efficient and exceptionally usable.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will read the `src/App.tsx` file to see how we can update the new meeting handler to optionally preset the selected date."
