  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing Sidebar Toggles**\n\nI\'m now fully immersed in designing and implementing `src/components/Sidebar.tsx`. My current focus is integrating toggle functionality at the bottom of the sidebar to switch between monthly/weekly calendar views and a list view. I aim to create an intuitive and aesthetically pleasing toggle, initially using the text \"\354\272\230\353\246\260\353\215\224\353\241\234 \353\263\264\352\270\260\" as the button to toggle the calendar view.\n\n\n**Refining Calendar Headers**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the calendar headers. I\'ve decided on the \"\354\272\230\353\246\260\353\215\224 \353\202\240\354\247\234 \355\225\204\355\204\260\" title with the calendar icon, and now I\'m structuring the monthly/weekly mode selector as `[ \354\233\224\352\260\204 \353\267\260 ] [ \354\243\274\352\260\204 \353\267\260 ]`.  Prev/Next navigation is key, so I\'m implementing hover animations and showing the year/month/week description clearly. For week view, the date range format will be `YYYY.MM.DD - MM.DD`.\n\n\n**Visualizing Event Indicators**\n\nI\'m now focusing on visually representing meetings within the calendar. I\'m exploring indicators for each day: a small gold dot `\342\227\217`, a meeting count like `(1)`, or even a small badge. The goal is to make it clear which days have meetings, especially with the use of a gold color for highlighting meetings. I\'ve also thought about a small pill indicator or text under dates.\n\n**Implementing Date Selection**\n\nI\'ve been working on the date selection behavior. Clicking a date will set `selectedDateStr` to `YYYY-MM-DD`. I\'m considering making the selection toggleable - click again to deselect, or offer a \"\355\225\204\355\204\260 \355\225\264\354\240\234\" button. Finally, the selected date will have a gold/white round ring highlight.\n\n\n**Defining Calendar Filtering Logic**\n\nI\'ve just added an exceptional feature! The calendar filters meetings based on the currently viewed range \342\200\223 month or week \342\200\223 unless a specific day is selected. This results in automatic filtering to the month or week. If a day is chosen, the list filters to show meetings for that exact day. If there are no meetings, a friendly message will appear.\n\n\n**Calculating Date Ranges**\n\nI\'m now focusing on implementing the date range filtering. I\'ve figured out how to filter meetings within the currently visible month, easily checking if `meetingDate.startsWith(YYYY-MM)`. For week filtering, I\'m calculating the Sunday and Saturday dates of the week to create a `[startOfWeekStr, endOfWeekStr]` range and check the date accordingly. The `YYYY-MM-DD` format is critical for comparisons.\n\n\n**Structuring Sidebar Implementation**\n\nI\'m now fully immersed in developing the new `/src/components/Sidebar.tsx` file. I\'ve preserved all core functionalities like live search, list item design, and callback handling for add/delete/select actions. The UI structure keeps the left header, \"\354\203\210 \355\232\214\354\235\230 \354\266\224\352\260\200\355\225\230\352\270\260\" button, and handles list and calendar views based on the `viewMode` state. The calendar control panel includes the month/week toggles, prev/next navigation, weekday display, and date cells with proper padding for a full monthly view. I am using all styling classes and e-land colors.\n\n\n**Finalizing Component Implementation**\n\nI\'m now putting the finishing touches on the sidebar component implementation. I\'ve ensured a visually clean separation for the date selection highlights and meeting indicators within the calendar. I\'ve also incorporated the view mode switcher at the bottom and a systems environment footer. Plus, I\'ve integrated a filter reset button and focused on correctly importing and using the necessary `lucide-react` icons, including `ChevronLeft` and `ChevronRight` for calendar navigation. The week number and date labels for the weekly view are now working as expected.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will update `src/components/Sidebar.tsx` to add a highly-customized, beautiful Monthly / Weekly calendar view date-filter mechanism at the bottom, complete with its own view modes, easy date selections, visual meeting counters, and a seamless toggle above the footer."
